menu "ACRouter ESP-NOW Source (v2.0 wireless)"

config ACROUTER_ESPNOW_SOURCE
    bool "Enable ESP-NOW wireless measurement source"
    # ESP-NOW is an ESP32-tier feature only: default ON for the ESP32 full build,
    # OFF for every other target (ESP32-C2 uses wired DimmerLink-I2C, not ESP-NOW).
    # Encoding the policy here (not just in a defaults layer) makes it robust to a
    # stale generated sdkconfig flipping it on for the C2 (operator decision 2026-07-17).
    default y if IDF_TARGET_ESP32
    default n
    help
        Receive rbAmp measurements from wireless nodes over ESP-NOW (rbgrid wire
        protocol) and feed them into the Sensor Hub as ACROUTER_SOURCE_ESPNOW
        events (priority 0), the same merge path the internal ADC and rbAmp I2C
        sources use.

        Minimal scope: RX rbAmp REALTIME only, open (unencrypted) bring-up. No
        master/PTP time-sync, no period/billing. Dimmer control TX to nodes is a
        later addition. Safe to enable with no node present.

if ACROUTER_ESPNOW_SOURCE

config ACROUTER_ESPNOW_CHANNEL
    int "Force WiFi/ESP-NOW channel (0 = keep current)"
    default 0
    range 0 13
    help
        ESP-NOW peers must share one WiFi channel. 0 = use ACRouter's current
        WiFi channel (AP channel, or the router's channel in STA mode) and have
        the node match it. Set >0 only if you need to pin a specific channel
        (may disrupt an STA uplink).

endif

endmenu
